Definition: from an unused root meaning to prick; a prong, i.e. hay-fork; fork.
from {{h7043}}; insubstantial; light.
intensive from {{h7049}}; a slinger; slinger.
from {{h7049}}; a sling; also a (door) screen (as if slung across), or the valve (of the door) itself; hanging, leaf, sling.
or קִימוֹשׁ; from an unused root meaning to sting; a prickly plant; nettle. Compare {{h7063}}.
from {{h6965}}; an elevation; Kamon, a place East of the Jordan; Camon.
from {{h6965}} and {{h410}}; raised of God; Kemuel, the name of a relative of Abraham, and of two Israelites; Kemuel.
feminine of active participle of {{h6965}}; something that rises, i.e. a stalk of grain; (standing) corn, grown up, stalk.
a primitive root; to pluck, i.e. destroy; cut down, fill with wrinkles.
from an unused root probably meaning to grind; flour; flour, meal.
intensive from {{h7046}}; ridicule; mocking.
a primitive root; to sling; also to carve (as if a circular motion, or into light forms); carve, sling (out).
from {{h7043}}; brightened (as if sharpened); burnished, polished.
from {{h7043}}; vilification; (ac-) curse(-d, -ing).
a primitive root; to disparage, i.e. ridicule; mock, scoff, scorn.
from {{h7046}}; a laughing-stock; derision.
from {{h7043}}; frivolous; Kallai, an Israelite; Kallai.
from {{h7034}}; insignificance; Kelajah, an Israelite; Kelaiah.
from {{h7038}}; maiming; Kelita, the name of three Israelites; Kelita.

a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) light, literally (swift, small, sharp, etc.) or figuratively (easy, trifling, vile, etc.); abate, make bright, bring into contempt, (ac-) curse, despise, (be) ease(-y, -ier), (be a, make, make somewhat, move, seem a, set) light(-en, -er, -ly, -ly afflict, -ly esteem, thing), × slight(-ly), be swift(-er), (be, be more, make, re-) vile, whet.
or קָלִיא; from {{h7033}}; roasted ears of grain; parched corn.
a primitive root; to maim; lacking in his parts.
contracted from {{h7043}}; light; (by implication) rapid (also adverbial); light, swift(-ly).
(Aramaic) of Greek origin; a lyre; harp.
a primitive root (rather identical with {{h7034}} through the idea of shrinkage by heat); to toast, i.e. scorch partially or slowly; dried, loathsome, parch, roast.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h6963}}; sound, voice.
for {{h6950}}; to assemble; gather together.
a primitive root; to be light (as implied in rapid motion), but figuratively, only (be [causatively, hold] in contempt); base, contemn, despise, lightly esteem, set light, seem vile.
apparently but a form for {{h6747}}; a kettle; caldron.
from {{h7034}}; disgrace; (by implication) the pudenda; confusion, dishonour, ignominy, reproach, shame.
from {{h6983}}; winding; Kishon, a river of Palestine; Kishon, Kison.
from {{h6983}}; bowed; Kishi, an Israelite; Kishi.
from {{h7036}}; intense disgrace; shameful spewing.
or קִר; (Isaiah 22:5), or (feminine) קִירָה; from {{h6979}}; a wall (as built in a trench); mason, side, town, × very, wall.
from {{h6972}}; terminal; out-(utter-) most.
perhaps from {{h7006}}; the gourd (as nauseous); gourd.
or קֵרֹס; from the same as {{h7166}}; ankled; Keros, one of the Nethinim; Keros.
from {{h6983}}; a bow; Kish, the name of five Israelites; Kish.
the same as {{h7023}}; fortress; Kir, a place in Assyrian; also one in Moab; Kir. Compare {{h7025}}.
or (feminine of the latter word) קִיר חֲרֶשֶׂת; from {{h7023}} and {{h2789}}; fortress of earthenware; Kir-Cheres or Kir-Chareseth, a place in Moab; Kir-haraseth, Kir-hareseth, Kirharesh, Kir-heres.
or קִינִי; (1 Chronicles 2:55), patronymic from {{h7014}}; a Kenite or member of the tribe of Kajin; Kenite.
the same as {{h7015}}; Kinah, a place in Palestine; Kinah.
from {{h6969}}; a dirge (as accompanied by beating the breasts or on instruments); lamentation.
the same as {{h7013}} (with a play upon the affinity to {{h7069}}); Kajin, the name of the first child, also of a place in Palestine, and of an Oriental tribe; Cain, Kenite(-s).
from {{h6969}} in the original sense of fixity; a lance (as striking fast); spear.
from {{h6965}}; an arising; rising up.
(Aramaic) from {{h6966}}; permanent (as rising firmly); stedfast, sure.
(Aramaic) from {{h6966}}; an edict (as arising in law); decree, statute.
from {{h6972}}; harvest (as the crop), whether the product (grain or fruit) or the (dry) season; summer (fruit, house).
from the same as {{h7064}}; fixed; Kenan, an antediluvian; Cainan, Kenan.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h7000}}; a knot (as tied up), i.e. (figuratively) a riddle; also a vertebra (as if a knot); doubt, joint.
from {{h6999}}; perfume; incense.
from {{h6999}}; fumigative; Kitron, a place in Palestine; Kitron.
from {{h6999}}; a fumigation; (sweet) incense, perfume.
from {{h6996}}; littleness; Kattath, a place in Palestine; Kattath.
a primitive root; to vomit; spue.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7019}}; harvest; summer.
or קִיטֹר; from {{h6999}}; a fume, i.e. cloud; smoke, vapour.
from {{h6965}}; an opponent (as rising against one), i.e. (collectively) enemies; substance.
and (feminine) קִצְוָה; from {{h7096}}; (used like {{h7097}}, but with less variety); a limit; end, edge, uttermost participle
feminine of {{h7097}}; (used like {{h7097}}); a termination; coast, corner, (selv-) edge, lowest, (uttermost) participle

or (negative only) קֵצֶה; from {{h7096}}; (used in a great variety of applications and idioms; compare {{h7093}}); an extremity; × after, border, brim, brink, edge, end, (in-) finite, frontier, outmost coast, quarter, shore, (out-) side, × some, ut(-ter-) most (part).
a primitive root; to cut off; (figuratively) to destroy; (partially) to scrape off; cut off, cut short, scrape (off).
from {{h7094}}; shape (as if cut out); base (as if there cut off); bottom, size.
a primitive root; to clip, or (generally) chop; cut down, shorn.
contracted from {{h7112}}; an extremity; adverbially (with prepositional prefix) after; after, (utmost) border, end, (in-) finite, × process.
a primitive root; to draw together, i.e. close; by implication, to leap (by contracting the limbs); specifically, to die (from gathering up the feet); shut (up), skip, stop, take out of the way.
from an unused root meaning to contract, i.e.; spring forward; an arrow-snake (as darting on its prey); great owl.
or קִפֹּדlemma קִכֹּד kaf, corrected to קִפֹּד; from {{h7088}}; a species of bird, perhaps the bittern (from its contracted form); bittern.
from {{h7069}}; creation, i.e. (concretely) creatures; also acquisition, purchase, wealth; getting, goods, × with money, riches, substance.
patronymic from {{h7073}},; a Kenizzite or descendant of Kenaz; Kenezite, Kenizzites.
a primitive root; to erect; but used only as denominative from {{h7064}}; to nestle, i.e. build or occupy as a nest; make...nest.
from an unused root (meaning to erect); cinnamon bark (as in upright rolls); cinnamon.
feminine of {{h7070}}; reediness; Kanah, the name of a stream and of a place in Palestine; Kanah.

from {{h7069}}; a reed (as erect); by resemblance a rod (especially for measuring), shaft, tube, stem, the radius (of the arm), beam (of a steelyard); balance, bone, branch, calamus, cane, reed, × spearman, stalk.
probably from an unused root meaning to hunt; hunter; Kenaz, the name of an Edomite and of two Israelites; Kenaz.
for {{h7067}}; jealous or angry; jealous.
from {{h7069}}; possession; Kenath, a place East of the Jordan; Kenath.
from an unused root probably meaning to wrench; perversion; end.
a primitive root; to contract, i.e. roll together; cut off.
from {{h7088}}; shrinking, i.e., terror; destruction.
a primitive root; properly, to distribute, i.e. determine by lot or magical scroll; by implication, to divine; divine(-r, -ation), prudent, soothsayer, use (divination).
from {{h7080}}; a lot; also divination (including its fee), oracle; (reward of) divination, divine sentence, witchcraft.
a primitive root; to lop off; cut off.
from the same as {{h3563}} (or as {{h7185}}); properly, a cup, i.e. an ink-stand; inkhorn.
perhaps from {{h7049}} in the sense of enclosing; citadel; Keilah, a place in Palestine; Keilah.
from the same as {{h6970}}; an incision or gash; mark.
probably from {{h7167}}; a bowl (as cut out hollow); charger, dish.
a primitive root; to shrink, i.e. thicken (as unracked wine, curdled milk, clouded sky, frozen water); congeal, curdle, dark, settle.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7069}}; to purchase; buy.
from {{h7065}}; jealous; jealous. Compare {{h7072}}.
contracted from {{h7077}}; a nest (as fixed), sometimes including the nestlings; figuratively, a chamber or dwelling; nest, room.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) zealous, i.e. (in a bad sense) jealous or envious; (be) envy(-ious), be (move to, provoke to) jealous(-y), × very, (be) zeal(-ous).
from {{h7061}}; a grasp, i.e. handful; handful.
from the same as {{h7057}}; a prickly plant; thorn.
a primitive root; to wither; hew down, wither.
a primitive root; to grasp with the hand; take an handful.
from an unused root apparently meaning to incise; fennel-flower (from its pungency); fitches.
from {{h7065}}; jealousy or envy; envy(-ied), jealousy, × sake, zeal.

a primitive root; to erect, i.e. create; by extension, to procure, especially by purchase (causatively, sell); by implication to own; attain, buy(-er), teach to keep cattle, get, provoke to jealousy, possess(-or), purchase, recover, redeem, × surely, × verily.
